      • getIssued

        public String getIssued()
        Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the catalog, as specified by dct:issued Note DCAT standard requires dates in string format to be ISO 8601 Date and Time compliant string format i.e. "2011-12-11". In TraceProv if date format is unknown prepend it with "unparseable:" to avoid confusing it with regular dates. If date is unknown the empty string is used.
        Overrides:
        getIssued in class ADcatCatalog
        See Also:
        ADcatDataset.getIssued(), ADcatDistribution.getIssued(), ADcatCatalogRecord.getIssued()

      • getLanguages

        public com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList<Locale> getLanguages()
        The languages of the catalog. This refers to the language used in the textual metadata describing titles, descriptions, etc. of the datasets in the catalog. The publisher might also choose to describe the language on the dataset level. Java Locale should be created out of language codes defined by the Library of Congress ( ISO 639-1, ISO 639-2). If a ISO 639-1 (two-letter) code is defined for language, then its corresponding IRI should be used; if no ISO 639-1 code is defined, then IRI corresponding to the ISO 639-2 (three-letter) code should be used.
        Specified by:
        getLanguages in class ADcatCatalog
        See Also:
        ADcatDataset.getLanguages()

      • getLicense

        public String getLicense()
        This links to the license document under which the catalog is made available and not the datasets. Even if the license of the catalog applies to all of its datasets and distributions, it should be replicated on each distribution. Specified by dct:license
        Overrides:
        getLicense in class ADcatCatalog

      • getModified

        public String getModified()
        Most recent date on which the catalog was changed, updated or modified. Must be in a ISO 8601 Date and Time compliant string format i.e. "2011-12-11" . Specified by dct:modified In TraceProv if date format is unknown prepend it with "unparseable:" to avoid confusing it with regular dates. If date is unknown the empty string is used.
        Overrides:
        getModified in class ADcatCatalog

      • getRights

        public String getRights()
        This describes the rights under which the catalog can be used/reused and not the datasets . Even if these rights apply to all the catalog datasets and distributions, it should be replicated on each distribution. Specified by dct:rights.
        Overrides:

      • getThemes

        public ASkosConceptScheme getThemes()
        The taxonomy of themes used to classify catalog's datasets, as specified by dcat: themeTaxonomy . Notice that 'category' is also used as synonym of 'themes' in dcat specs. When field is not available SkosConceptScheme.of() is returned.
        Overrides:
        getThemes in class ADcatCatalog
        See Also:
        ADcatDataset.getThemes()
